    "description": {
        "en-US": "Markdown Here Revival lets you write email in Markdown and render it (make it pretty!) before sending.\n\nVery easy to use:\n1. Write your email in Markdown.\n2. Click the Markdown Toggle button in the format toolbar\n3. It's pretty!\n\nThis is an open source project forked from Markdown Here to support modern Thunderbird versions.\n\nKNOWN BUGS (v3.2.5):\n<b>If you have problems with Markdown not rendering after updating to v3.2.5</b>, (highlights the message and nothing happens), try changing the Syntax Highlight CSS in MDHR Options-&gt;Themes.\nAn update with a fix is on the way.\nMath rendering is not working after updating. It can be fixed by adjusting TeX Mathematical Formulae Support in Options. See the screenshot for the correct value. \n\nPermissions explanation:\nThis addon makes use of the \"experiments\" API, resulting in the permissions prompt requesting \"unrestricted access\". This is the case with any Thunderbird addon that uses the experiments API. This is how MDHR displays notification bars in the compose window. (See screenshot)\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1674002\">Bug 1674002</a> will implement the NotificationBar Mai Extension API in Thunderbird."
    },
